<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Multi-Victim Cluster Handoff — {{ cluster.public_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
<style>
  /* Aggregated cluster handoff — one document covering N victims.
     The intended audience is an AUSA / DOJ section chief weighing
     whether to prioritize a multi-victim filing. Visual emphasis
     therefore goes on the AGGREGATE numbers (combined loss, victim
     count) before any per-victim detail. */
  .cluster-headline {
    background: #fafafa;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold-accent);
    padding: 22px 28px;
    margin: 20px 0 28px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .cluster-stat {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-right: 32px;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .cluster-stat-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-quiet);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }
  .cluster-stat-value {
    display: block;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Multi-Victim Cluster Handoff</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Cluster {{ cluster.public_id }}</div>
    <h1>Multi-Victim<br/>Cluster Handoff</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      This deliverable consolidates {{ cluster.member_case_count }}
      Recupero-traced cases that share perpetrator infrastructure
      into a single law-enforcement filing. Each case retains its
      own per-victim freeze brief and trace report; this document
      surfaces the cluster-level facts that justify a consolidated
      enforcement response.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="cluster-headline">
  <div class="cluster-stat">
    <span class="cluster-stat-label">Cluster ID</span>
    <span class="cluster-stat-value">{{ cluster.public_id }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="cluster-stat">
    <span class="cluster-stat-label">Victims represented</span>
    <span class="cluster-stat-value">{{ cluster.member_case_count }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="cluster-stat">
    <span class="cluster-stat-label">Aggregate loss</span>
    <span class="cluster-stat-value">{{ cluster.total_loss_usd_human }}</span>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>1. Why these cases belong together</h2>
<p>
  Cross-case correlation against Recupero's cumulative address
  index identifies a common perpetrator-controlled wallet that
  appears in every member case. The seed binding wallet for this
  cluster is:
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Seed address</th>
    <td class="mono">{{ cluster.seed_perp_address }}</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th>Chain</th>
    <td>{{ cluster.seed_perp_chain }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% if cluster.shared_perp_addresses and cluster.shared_perp_addresses|length > 1 %}
  <tr>
    <th>Additional binding wallets</th>
    <td class="small">
      {% for addr in cluster.shared_perp_addresses %}
      {% if addr != cluster.seed_perp_address %}
      <span class="mono">{{ addr }}</span><br/>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </td>
  </tr>
  {% endif %}
  <tr>
    <th>First observed</th>
    <td>{{ cluster.created_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") if cluster.created_at else "—" }}</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th>Latest case joined</th>
    <td>{{ cluster.updated_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") if cluster.updated_at else "—" }}</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>2. Member cases</h2>
<p class="small">
  Cases sorted by the order in which they joined the cluster. The
  "originator" is the first case Recupero observed for this
  perpetrator infrastructure; subsequent cases "joined" via shared
  wallets.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>#</th>
      <th>Case identifier</th>
      <th>Role</th>
      <th>Joined via</th>
      <th>Loss</th>
      <th>Joined at</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for m in cluster.members %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
      <td class="mono small">
        {% if m.case_id %}{{ m.case_id }}{% else %}{{ m.investigation_id }}{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>{{ m.role }}</td>
      <td class="mono small">
        {# v0.23.1 (audit-fix HIGH-1): full None-guard, not just on the
           tail slice. Pre-v0.23.1 m.joined_via_address[:10] raised
           TypeError on None — caught by render_cluster_handoff's
           try/except and surfaced as "cluster not found or render
           failed", which is incorrect (the cluster exists). #}
        {% if m.joined_via_address %}
        {{ m.joined_via_address[:10] }}…{{ m.joined_via_address[-6:] }}
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="amount">
        {% if m.case_total_loss_usd %}${{ "{:,.2f}".format(m.case_total_loss_usd|float) }}{% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="small">
        {{ m.joined_at.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") if m.joined_at else "—" }}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>3. Recommended consolidated action</h2>
<p>
  The combined aggregate loss of
  <strong>{{ cluster.total_loss_usd_human }}</strong> across
  {{ cluster.member_case_count }} victims supports the case for a
  coordinated multi-victim filing rather than individual victim
  pursuits. Recommended next steps:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Identify the assigned AUSA for each member case</strong>
    (if any) and convene a cross-jurisdictional coordination call.
    Per-case freeze briefs and trace reports are available in the
    individual case folders; this document is the cluster-level
    summary they share.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>File a consolidated freeze request</strong> with the
    issuers named across all member cases. The aggregate dollar
    threshold typically commands faster compliance-team response
    than the per-case requests on their own.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Pursue OFAC designation review</strong> for the
    binding wallet(s) when the aggregate loss meets the
    investigative threshold (typically $5M+). The consolidated
    cluster materials are appropriate for that submission.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Engage FBI Cyber Division</strong>'s multi-victim
    matter intake — clusters that meet a $10M aggregate threshold
    and span ≥10 victims typically qualify for priority-target
    status, which materially affects the speed of subpoena
    issuance to non-cooperating exchanges.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>4. Per-case forensic deliverables</h2>
<p class="small">
  Every case in this cluster carries its own complete forensic
  package — trace report, fund-flow diagram, per-issuer freeze
  requests, and individual LE handoff. The cluster's case
  identifiers above are the keys to retrieve those packages from
  the Recupero case store. This consolidated handoff is intended
  to support cross-case coordination, not to replace the
  per-case records.
</p>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ cluster.public_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Strictly Confidential.</span>
    Intended for the receiving federal agency / coordinating counsel.
    Not for distribution to victims, defendants, or issuer
    compliance teams — those audiences are served by the
    per-case deliverables.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
